MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   BERN, Switzerland -- Switzerland's trade deficit narrowed
in May to 915.5 million Swiss francs ($646.3 million) from a
revised gap of 1.15 billion francs in April, the government
said. In May 1989, the revised trade deficit was 1.19 billion
francs.
   Imports in May expanded to 8.61 billion francs from a
revised 8.16 billion francs in April, and exports climbed to
7.69 billion francs from a revised 7.01 billion francs.
</LP>
