<LP>
   MCCONNELLSBURG, Pa. -- JLG Industries Inc. said its board
accepted the immediate resignation of Stephen R. Cecil as
president and chief operating officer of the hydraulic
machinery producer.
   Mr. Cecil, 47 years old, who also resigned from the board,
is pursuing other business interests, the company said. His
duties will be assumed by John L. Grove, chairman and chief
executive officer, until the board names a new president. JLG
said the board's search for a successor is expected to be
completed shortly.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Grove, 69, said in an interview that he was saddened
by Mr. Cecil's departure, which he described as friendly.
