<HL>
   International Brief -- Bayer AG:
   Earnings for 5 Months Fell
   On 2.2% Decline in Sales
</HL>
<DATE>
06/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   G.BAY
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Bayer AG of West Germany, a chemical concern, said that
its group earnings declined in the first five months of this
year, though it didn't disclose profit figures, and that
group sales fell 2.2% to 18.25 billion marks ($10.89 billion)
from 18.66 billion marks a year earlier.
   The announcement at Bayer's annual meeting confirmed
expectations of falling profits in the West German chemical
industry, following several years of record results. Bayer
said foreign-exchange fluctuations alone reduced its sales by
about one billion marks and also depressed earnings.
</LP>
