06/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   TOPPC
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Topps Co. reported record results for its first quarter on
strong growth in its staple baseball card and Bazooka bubble
gum lines but particularly in its newer products featuring
Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and New Kids on the Block.
   Topps, based in New York, reported net income of $13.9
million, or 44 cents a share, for the quarter ended June 2.
In the comparable quarter last year, net was $8.5 million, or
27 cents a share. Sales rose to $86.2 million from $62.8
million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   During the quarter, the company said, it paid $25 million
of long-term debt, reducing its total debt to $60 million.
   Topps shares closed yesterday at $22, unchanged, in
national over-the-counter trading.
