   Business Brief -- Humana Inc.:
   Conversion Program Attracts
   99% of Subordinated Debt
</HL>
<DATE>
06/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14
</SO>
<CO>
   HUM
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Humana Inc., Louisville, Ky., said 99% of its nearly $200
million face amount of convertible subordinated debentures
were converted into 5,249,000 of its common shares.
   The debentures, due Aug. 15, 2009, were converted at a
price of $37.80 a share, which equals 26.455 common shares
per $1,000 principal amount of debentures.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Remaining debentures will be redeemed July 2 at $1,042.50
plus accrued interest of $32.35 from Feb. 15 through July 2.
   Humana owns and operates 85 hospital and health benefit
plans for groups and Medicare beneficiaries. A company
spokesman said Humana has 104,087,000 common shares after the
conversion.
