<HL>
   International Brief -- Bank Leu:
   Majority of Voting Shares
   Back a CS Holding Alliance
</HL>
<DATE>
06/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   Z.LEU Z.CSU
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Bank Leu, Switzerland's fifth-largest commercial bank,
said holders of a majority of the bank's voting shares are
willing to accept a proposed alliance with CS Holding AG
through a new holding company that CS Holding will control.
Terms haven't been disclosed.
   As a result, Bank Leu scheduled a special meeting of
holders for Tuesday to vote on approving the transaction.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The new holding company, to be called Leu Holding, would
be composed of Bank Leu and two small investment houses
already in the CS Holding group, Bank Hofmann and Clariden
Bank. Among CS Holding's other units is Credit Suisse, the
country's third-largest commercial bank. Bank Leu's board on
May 11 recommended that shareholders accept the CS Holding
offer to swap Bank Leu shares for shares in the new holding
company.
